   "source": [
    "## Headline\n",
    "\n",
    "> `default_warmstart_zyx` leaves **≥60 µm of median Z residual** on both good subjects. XY is near-perfect (13–38 µm). The Z residual is driven almost entirely by *sz* error: ICP converges to sz = 3.36 / 2.25 when truth is 2.82 / 3.04 (errors **+19 %** and **−26 %**).\n",
    ">\n",
    "> Pinning sxy from ROI-area leaves that failure in place. Pinning **sz** to the true value drops median residual to 25 µm on 790322 and 49 µm on 788406 — so **sz is the binding constraint**, not sxy, not R, not t_xy. Surfaces give a usable Z-translation anchor (HCR pia → CZ pia) and a **bounded** sz prior via HCR cortex thickness / CZ cortex span. Bound width is ≈1.33×."
   ]
