    "**Read-out.**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **A regresses**: injecting only sxy keeps ICP's wrong sz and the Z offset *worsens* because the pinned t_z stops ICP from absorbing scale error into translation.\n",
    "2. **B helps 788406, fails 790322**: surface-thickness × 0.90 under-shoots the true sz on 790322 (CZ extends past HCR cortex). The 0.90 coverage assumption is the thing that breaks.\n",
    "3. **C is dramatic**: sxy + oracle sz is a clean win on both subjects, beating LM-perfect on each (R fixed at exactly 180° absorbs less noise than a free R fit).\n",
    "4. The B→C gap (138 → 25 µm on 790322) is the ceiling on what a surface-only sz prior can deliver — so surfaces must supply a **bounded sz search range**, not a point estimate."
   ]
  },
